subject: p19454978
Findings: Endotracheal tube terminates 46 cm above the carina and right internal jugular line ending at mid SVC are appropriate. No interval changes in the lungs since. Bibasal atelectasis, left side more than right side, is unchanged. Top normal heart size, mediastinal and hilar contours are stable in appearance. No new lung opacities of concern. Pleural effusion, if any, is mild on the left side and similar.
